Schools in the South Korean capital Seoul and nearby areas resumed in-person classes for the first time in almost a month on Monday after daily coronavirus cases dropped to the lowest levels since mid-August.Students returned to schools under a hybrid schedule of in-person and online classes to limit the number of people at schools at any given time.Reuters 
